Michael Mahoney







 
 





Michael F. Mahoney




Michael F. Mahoney, age 51, has served as a director of Baxter since October 2015.
Mahoney is chairman, president and chief executive officer at Boston Scientific Corporation and a member of the company’s board of directors. He first joined Boston Scientific in 2011, with a 24-year track record of building market-leading medical device, capital equipment and healthcare IT businesses.  Prior to joining Boston Scientific, Mahoney served as worldwide chairman of Johnson & Johnson medical devices and diagnostics division and served as worldwide group chairman of Johnson & Johnson’s DePuy orthopedics and neuro-science business.  He was president and chief executive officer of the Global Healthcare Exchange, a leading supply chain solutions company, from 2001 to 2007 before joining Johnson & Johnson.  Earlier in his career, he advanced through a series of leadership roles at General Electric Medical Systems.  He serves as a director of AdvaMed and is a member of the American Heart Association CEO Roundtable.
 









